zhnFirewall.name: zhnFirewall
zhnFirewall.contactinfo: Zhone Technologies, Inc. Florida Design Center 8545 126th Avenue North Largo, FL 33773 Toll-Free: +1 877-ZHONE20 (+1 877-946-6320) Tel: +1-510-777-7000 Fax: +1-510-777-7001 E-mail: support@zhone.com
zhnFirewall.description: This file defines the private Enterprise MIB extensions that define LAN Management Access Service Filters and Port Forwarding objects supported by the Zhone CPEs.

FirewallMgmtAccessServiceValues.name: FirewallMgmtAccessServiceValues
FirewallMgmtAccessServiceValues.description: LAN Management Access Services that can be blocked from the CPEs management network.

FirewallMgmtAccessServiceActions.name: FirewallMgmtAccessServiceActions
FirewallMgmtAccessServiceActions.description: LAN Management Access Service actions to perform for the specified service.

FirewallPortProtocolValues.name: FirewallPortProtocolValues
FirewallPortProtocolValues.description: LAN Port Forwarding protocols that can be filtered, per port.

firewallMgmtAccessTable.name: firewallMgmtAccessTable
firewallMgmtAccessTable.description: Table of LAN Management Access Service Filters

firewallMgmtAccessEntry.name: firewallMgmtAccessEntry
firewallMgmtAccessEntry.description: Table of entries of LAN Management Access service filters. This table is used to configure management access on the device. It is useful in making the device management network by blocking protocols or services that are highly susceptible to external attacks.

firewallMgmtServiceIndex.name: firewallMgmtServiceIndex
firewallMgmtServiceIndex.description: LAN Management Access Services Table index. Enumerated values: Http (1), Https (2), Ping (3), Snmp (4), SnmpTrap (5), Ssh (6), Telnet (7)

firewallMgmtAction.name: firewallMgmtAction
firewallMgmtAction.description: LAN Management Access Service filtering action. Enumerated values: Allow (1), Deny (2), Undefined (3)

firewallPortForwardingTable.name: firewallPortForwardingTable
firewallPortForwardingTable.description: Table of LAN Port Forwarding Rules. Note that the rules in this table have no effect until the global firewall object (sysFirewallEnable) is enabled.

firewallPortForwardingEntry.name: firewallPortForwardingEntry
firewallPortForwardingEntry.description: This table is used to configure port forwarding firewall rules for the device.

firewallPortForwardingName.name: firewallPortForwardingName
firewallPortForwardingName.description: Descriptive name for a LAN Port Forwarding Rule.

firewallPortType.name: firewallPortType
firewallPortType.description: Enumerated value of: portRange (1), -- Range indicates that any traffic on those ports will be -- sent to the private IP address. portRemap (2), -- Remap indicates that any traffic on those ports will be -- sent to the private IP address at the private port. dmz (3) -- When DMZ is chosen it is the only rule allowed on that -- interface. A DMZ rule is effectively the same as a Range -- rule with all ports included. Range rules are more secure -- than setting a DMZ rule, because Range rules allow specific -- ports or groups of ports to be opened up.

firewallPortProtocol.name: firewallPortProtocol
firewallPortProtocol.description: Enumerated value of: tcp (1), udp (2), tcpOrUdp (3), icmp (4), icmpv4 (5), none (6)

firewallPortPublicPortStart.name: firewallPortPublicPortStart
firewallPortPublicPortStart.description: Lowest value port number for the range.

firewallPortPublicPortEnd.name: firewallPortPublicPortEnd
firewallPortPublicPortEnd.description: Highest value port number for the range. This can be equal to firewallPortPublicPortStart if there is only one port.

firewallPortPrivatePort.name: firewallPortPrivatePort
firewallPortPrivatePort.description: The port number with which to send the traffic.

firewallPortPrivateIPAddress.name: firewallPortPrivateIPAddress
firewallPortPrivateIPAddress.description: The port IP Address with which to send the traffic.

firewallPortForwardingRowStatus.name: firewallPortForwardingRowStatus
firewallPortForwardingRowStatus.description: The SNMP RowStatus of the current row. The following objects must be specified upon row creation: firewallPortForwardingName firewallPortPrivateIPAddress

zhnFirewallCompliance.name: zhnFirewallCompliance
zhnFirewallCompliance.description: The Compliance statement for SNMP entities which manage the Zhone CPE LAN Firewall Management Access Services and Port Forwarding Information

zhnFirewallMgmtAccessGroup.name: zhnFirewallMgmtAccessGroup
zhnFirewallMgmtAccessGroup.description: A collection of Zhone IP objects that describe the LAN Management Access Services that can be filtered for a particular LAN interface.

zhnFirewallPortForwardingGroup.name: zhnFirewallPortForwardingGroup
zhnFirewallPortForwardingGroup.description: A collection of Zhone IP objects that describe the LAN Port Forwarding Management rules for filtering protocols and ports for a particular LAN interface.
